wp count attachments "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
====================================================================

NAME
----

wp count attachments - Count number of attachments for the mime type(s).

SYNOPSIS
--------

Count number of attachments for the mime type(s).

If you set the optional mime\_type parameter, then an array will still
be returned, but will only have the item you are looking for. It does
not give you the number of attachments that are children of a post. You
can get that by counting the number of children that post has.

USAGE
-----

` <?php wp_count_attachments( $mime_type ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$mime_type` 
:   ([*string|array*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String.7Carray "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Optional. Array or comma-separated list of MIME
    patterns.
    Default:

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `` `(array)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   Number of posts for each mime type.

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: [2.5](/Version_2.5 "Version 2.5")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`wp_count_attachments()` is located in `wp-includes/post.php`

